UID:ai-training-s01-20260310@patricioperezbla
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260310T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260310T130000
SUMMARY:AI Workspace Training – Session 1: The AI Coding Revolution
DESCRIPTION:AI Workspace Training Program — Session 1 of 11\n\nPresented by: Patricio Perez\, Tech Lead — Node Backend Team\n\n📋 THIS SESSION\nSession 1: The AI Coding Revolution (Non-technical · 60 min)\n• What is an LLM? (5-min explainer\, no jargon)\n• From ChatGPT to coding agents: the evolution 2020–2026\n• What is Claude Code? Live demo of a real task\n• Business value: productivity gains\, code quality\, knowledge retention\n• What Claude Code is NOT\n• Homework: Install Claude Code\, complete one task\, share results\n\n📅 FULL SCHEDULE\nWeek 1:\n  Tue Mar 10 – S1: The AI Coding Revolution\n  Thu Mar 12 – S2: How Claude Code Works\n  Fri Mar 13 – S3: Getting Started with the Workspace\nWeek 2:\n  Tue Mar 17 – S4: Skills\, Hooks & Commands\n  Thu Mar 19 – S5: Memory Strategies for AI Agents\nWeek 3:\n  Tue Mar 24 – S6: The Self-Improving Agent\n  Thu Mar 26 – S7: Agent Orchestration\, MCP & CLI Tools\nWeek 4:\n  Tue Mar 31 – S8: Designer & QA Workflows\n  Thu Apr  2 – S9: Advanced Patterns & Tips\nWeek 5:\n  Tue Apr  7 – S10: Workshop\n  Thu Apr  9 – S11: Adoption Playbook & Retrospective\n\n⚙️ REQUIREMENTS\n• All participants: GitHub account\, Claude Code access\n• Sessions 4–11: Laptop with Node.js 18+\, Docker Desktop\n• Recommended: VS Code or terminal comfort\n\n📊 Attendance is tracked for each session (billing purposes).\n\n📊 COURSE SLIDES\n• Live (animated): https://patricioperezbla.github.io/ai-workspace-training/\n• PDF download: https://patricioperezbla.github.io/ai-workspace-training/ai-workspace-training_v10.pdf
