SUMMARY:AI Workspace Training – Session 4: Skills, Hooks & Commands
DESCRIPTION:AI Workspace Training Program — Session 4 of 11\n\nPresented by: Patricio Perez\, Tech Lead — Node Backend Team\n\n📋 THIS SESSION\nSession 4: Skills\, Hooks & Commands (Technical · 60 min)\n• Skills system: domain expertise auto-loaded on demand\n• Hooks system: lifecycle events for quality enforcement\n• Code quality hooks: block 'as any'\, block hardcoded secrets\, warn on debug code\n• Slash commands: /commit\, /debug\, /pr-review\, /session-review\n• How to create your own skill (live walkthrough)\n• Homework: Create a skill for your team's conventions\n\n📅 FULL SCHEDULE\nWeek 2 (this week):\n  Tue Mar 17 – S4: Skills\, Hooks & Commands\n  Thu Mar 19 – S5: Memory Strategies for AI Agents\nFull schedule:\n  Mar 10\, 12\, 13 – S1\, S2\, S3 (completed)\n  Mar 17\, 19 – S4\, S5\n  Mar 24\, 26 – S6\, S7\n  Mar 31\, Apr 2 – S8\, S9\n  Apr 7\, 9 – S10\, S11\n\n⚙️ REQUIREMENTS\n• Node.js 18+\, Docker Desktop\n• VS Code or terminal comfort recommended\n\n📊 Attendance is tracked for each session (billing purposes).\n\n📊 COURSE SLIDES\n• Live (animated): https://patricioperezbla.github.io/ai-workspace-training/\n• PDF download: https://patricioperezbla.github.io/ai-workspace-training/ai-workspace-training_v10.pdf
